headlines.description: — Shake Milton scored 31 points and Ben Simmons had 10 points, 10 assists and 12 rebounds to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 125-108 win over the Miami Heat on Thursday night.

events.name: Houston Rockets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Christian Wood had 27 points and 15 rebounds, and the Houston Rockets rallied to beat the San Antonio Spurs 109-105 on Thursday night in their first game since trading away franchise cornerstone James Harden.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets rally past Spurs 109-105 in 1st game without Harden

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 18 of his 23 points in the second half to help Denver overcome the blazing shooting of Stephen Curry as the Nuggets held off the Golden State Warriors 114-104 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Nuggets hold off Curry, Warriors for 114-104 win

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 23 points and 15 rebounds to lead the Indiana Pacers past the Portland Trail Blazers 111-87 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis has 23 pts, 15 boards as Pacers down Blazers 111-87
